    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-04-16T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-04-16T06:00:00-05:00" n="438"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d438">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">881.00/4–1646: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bonsal</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">restricted</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-04-16T13:00:00+02:00"
                            >April 16, 1946—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received April 16—10:12 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>718. In course of conversation yesterday Acting Under Secretary Foreign Affairs
                    told me that Spanish Foreign Office after considerable discussion had decided
                    not to raise Tangier question thru diplomatic channels on expiration 6 months’
                    period of provisional regime. Acting Under Secretary, who is Aguirre de Career,
                    an expert on Tangier, said he had favored bringing matter up but that
                        Minister<note n="7" xml:id="d438fn7">Martin Artajo, Spanish Minister for
                        Foreign Affairs.</note> had overruled him.</p>
                <p>Sent Tangier Paris London by courier.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bonsal</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
